HEADWORD: Coquelicot
<hw>Coque"li*cot`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The wild poppy, or red corn
rose.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The color of the wild poppy; a color nearly red,
like orange mixed with scarlet.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Coquet</ent>⟦br⟧
